misconceptions.inferred_category_name: Computer 'understands' prompts / prompts control input parsing
misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that printing prompts like "Enter size:" and "Enter elements:" somehow guides the computer to read the right values (or that the prompts are part of the input logic).
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: In Java, prompts are just output text. They do not affect how Scanner reads input. Scanner reads tokens purely based on calls like nextInt(), regardless of what you printed. The program only works because the code explicitly calls nextInt() the right number of times, not because of the English messages.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: Usually no error; but can cause confusion when testing with automated graders (which may not expect extra prompt text) or when the student thinks the prompt changes what input is consumed.
